

-------- Grammar --------

rule 1 program: linebreak
rule 2 program: linebreak complete_commands linebreak
rule 3 complete_commands: complete_command
rule 4 complete_commands: complete_commands newline_list complete_command
rule 5 complete_command: list separator_op
rule 6 complete_command: list
rule 7 list: list separator_op and_or
rule 8 list: and_or
rule 9 and_or: pipeline
rule 10 and_or: and_or AND_IF linebreak pipeline
rule 11 and_or: and_or OR_IF linebreak pipeline
rule 12 pipeline: pipe_sequence
rule 13 pipe_sequence: command
rule 14 pipe_sequence: pipe_sequence "|" linebreak command
rule 15 command: simple_command
rule 16 simple_command: cmd_prefix cmd_word cmd_suffix
rule 17 simple_command: cmd_prefix cmd_word
rule 18 simple_command: cmd_prefix
rule 19 simple_command: cmd_name cmd_suffix
rule 20 simple_command: cmd_name
rule 21 cmd_name: WORD
rule 22 cmd_word: WORD
rule 23 cmd_prefix: io_redirect
rule 24 cmd_prefix: cmd_prefix io_redirect
rule 25 cmd_prefix: ASSIGNMENT_WORD
rule 26 cmd_prefix: cmd_prefix ASSIGNMENT_WORD
rule 27 cmd_suffix: io_redirect
rule 28 cmd_suffix: cmd_suffix io_redirect
rule 29 cmd_suffix: WORD
rule 30 cmd_suffix: cmd_suffix WORD
rule 31 io_redirect: io_file
rule 32 io_redirect: IO_NUMBER io_file
rule 33 io_file: "<" filename
rule 34 io_file: ">" filename
rule 35 io_file: DGREAT filename
rule 36 io_file: LESSGREAT filename
rule 37 io_file: CLOBBER filename
rule 38 filename: WORD
rule 39 separator_op: "&"
rule 40 separator_op: ";"
rule 41 newline_list: NEWLINE
rule 42 newline_list: newline_list NEWLINE
rule 43 linebreak: newline_list
rule 44 linebreak: 

------- Symbols -------

**Nonterminals, with rules where they appear

  $start (16)
    on right: 
    on left : 
  program (17)
    on right: 
    on left : 1 2
  linebreak (18)
    on right: 1 2 10 11 14
    on left : 43 44
  complete_commands (19)
    on right: 2 4
    on left : 3 4
  complete_command (20)
    on right: 3 4
    on left : 5 6
  newline_list (21)
    on right: 4 42 43
    on left : 41 42
  list (22)
    on right: 5 6 7
    on left : 7 8
  separator_op (23)
    on right: 5 7
    on left : 39 40
  and_or (24)
    on right: 7 8 10 11
    on left : 9 10 11
  pipeline (25)
    on right: 9 10 11
    on left : 12
  pipe_sequence (26)
    on right: 12 14
    on left : 13 14
  command (27)
    on right: 13 14
    on left : 15
  simple_command (28)
    on right: 15
    on left : 16 17 18 19 20
  cmd_prefix (29)
    on right: 16 17 18 24 26
    on left : 23 24 25 26
  cmd_word (30)
    on right: 16 17
    on left : 22
  cmd_suffix (31)
    on right: 16 19 28 30
    on left : 27 28 29 30
  cmd_name (32)
    on right: 19 20
    on left : 21
  io_redirect (33)
    on right: 23 24 27 28
    on left : 31 32
  io_file (34)
    on right: 31 32
    on left : 33 34 35 36 37
  filename (35)
    on right: 33 34 35 36 37
    on left : 38

**Terminals, with rules where they appear

  $end (0) 
  error (1) 
  WORD (2) 21 22 29 30 38
  ASSIGNMENT_WORD (3) 25 26
  IO_NUMBER (4) 32
  NEWLINE (5) 41 42
  AND_IF (6) 10
  OR_IF (7) 11
  DGREAT (8) 35
  LESSGREAT (9) 36
  CLOBBER (10) 37
  "|" (11) 14
  "<" (12) 33
  ">" (13) 34
  "&" (14) 39
  ";" (15) 40

--------- State ---------

state 0


  NEWLINE       shift, and go to state 3
  $default      reduce using rule 44 (linebreak)

  program       go to state 1
  linebreak     go to state 2
  newline_list  go to state 4

state 1


  $end          shift, and go to state 5


state 2

   1) program : linebreak _
